cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses strategies for identifying and prioritizing research studies for targeted validation, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on open-access publishing and scientific data science suggests cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as the most likely category. The use of data science techniques for identifying high-value research studies is relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases). The discussion of reproducibility and validation may also be relevant to cs.CY (Cryptography) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
